<h2 class="sectionedit1"><a name="fmod" id="fmod">fmod</a></h2>
<div class="level2">

<p>
Syntaxe :
</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">fmod</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">double</span> numerateur, <span class="kw4">double</span> denominateur<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span></pre>
<p>
La fonction <code>fmod()</code> renvoie le reste de la division
<code>numerateur</code> / <code>denominateur</code>.
</p>

<p>
Le C++ fournit également les implémentations suivantes :

</p>
<pre class="cpp code cpp">    <span class="co2">#include &lt;cmath&gt;</span>
    <span class="kw4">float</span> <span class="kw3">fmod</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">float</span> x, <span class="kw4">float</span> y<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// identique à fmodf() en C99</span>
    <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> <span class="kw3">fmod</span> <span class="br0">&#40;</span><span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> x, <span class="kw4">long</span> <span class="kw4">double</span> y<span class="br0">&#41;</span><span class="sy4">;</span> <span class="co1">// identique à fmodl() en C99</span></pre>
<p>
